The (extra) migrations you want to include for auto-management or self-management
docblock.long-description:
By default, on install/uninstall the resources/migrations folder will be checked for migrations. If you want to disable the auto install/uninstall behaviour, you can set this to false.
Optionally, if you want to specify optional migration folders you can add them in the array. If provided with true, those migrations will be auto installed/uninstalled. If provided false, those migrations will be made available by the vendor:publish command

Setting this to false, will disable automatic theme registration. Otherwise, the extension will automaticly register (if exists) the theme located at resources/theme and bind it to "vendor/package" aka the extensions slug.
Optionally, you can define other locations and namespaces.
